SIMPLE: serene
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Serene
<hw>Se*rene"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>serenus</ets> to grow dry, Gr. <?/<?/<?/ hot, scorching.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Bright; clear; unabscured; <as>as, a <ex>serene</ex>
sky</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The moon <qex>serene</qex> in glory mounts the sky.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Full many a gem of purest ray <qex>serene</qex>⟦br⟧
The dark unfathomed caves of ocean bear.</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Calm; placid; undisturbed; unruffled; <as>as, a
<ex>serene</ex> aspect; a <ex>serene</ex> soul</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In several countries of Europe, <xex>Serene</xex> is
given as a tittle to princes and the members of their families; as, His
<xex>Serene</xex> Highness.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Drop serene</b></col>. <fld>(Med.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Amaurosis</er>.</cd> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Serene</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Serene
<hw>Se*rene"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Serenity; clearness;
calmness.</def> <mark>[Poetic.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>serene</xex> of
heaven.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Southey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To their master is denied⟦br⟧
To share their sweet <qex>serene</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[F. <ets>serein</ets> evening dew or damp. See
<er>Serein</er>.]</ety> <def>Evening air; night chill.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Some <xex>serene</xex> blast me.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Serene</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Serene
<hw>Se*rene"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>serenare</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To make serene.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Heaven and earth, as if contending, vie⟦br⟧
To raise his being, and <qex>serene</qex> his soul.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Serenely</ent>⟦br⟧
